review_blob:
on tap in KL, if you like your coffee black--this is an interesting cloudy IPA --hops & citrus blend nicely with coffee aroma--with sweetness flowing as it goes on...not your typical one directional hop to the end IPA.
--
beer_name: Mikkeller Koppi Coffee IPA Citra & Michiti

review_blob:
Bottle shared with the guys here in KL recently--full of cocao, coconut, caramel with hints of vanilla aroma once the beer "warm up"--velvety, silky smooth but never overpowering with very well hidden abv---very tasty. A big thank you to the man himself--thank you Mr. Fox. This is a non-hyped up stout worth looking out for--grab it if you see one.

